I a survivor of childhood sexual abuse. To survive, I put the abuse in a box, in my soul to hold for me until I was strong enough to deal with it. The burden of carrying it around for me was the hardest.

I had to cut off a piece of me. I had to shut down my heart. I became hard on the inside. From the outside you couldn’t tell. It looked like I was living but I wasn’t’. In order to survive I had to keep the box closed tightly and as a result I could let nothing in. No light, no love. It was dark for a very long time. I aM heR
